stream
BT /F2 14 Tf 54 712.0 Td (Chapter 1: Understanding Chronic Pain) Tj ET
BT /F2 12 Tf 54 674.2 Td (Pain Science: What We Now Know) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 656.2 Td (Modern pain science reveals that chronic pain is NOT simply 'damage signals from tissues.') Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 642.2 Td (Pain is a complex output of the brain, influenced by biology, psychology, social context,) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 628.2 Td (beliefs, and emotions. This does NOT mean pain is 'in your head' - it is absolutely real.) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 614.2 Td (But understanding its complexity opens doors to more effective management.) Tj ET
BT /F2 11 Tf 54 586.4 Td (Acute vs. Chronic Pain) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 570.4 Td (- Acute pain: Protective alarm system. Usually proportional to tissue damage. Heals.) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 556.4 Td (- Chronic pain: Pain lasting 3+ months. Nervous system becomes sensitized. Pain) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 542.4 Td (signals amplified. Often not proportional to tissue state.) Tj ET
BT /F2 12 Tf 54 512.6 Td (Central Sensitization) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 494.6 Td (In chronic pain, the nervous system becomes 'turned up' like a volume dial. This means) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 480.6 Td (normal sensations can be perceived as painful, and painful stimuli feel more intense. This) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 466.6 Td (is a real neurological change, not imagined.) Tj ET
BT /F2 11 Tf 54 438.8 Td (Signs of Central Sensitization) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 422.8 Td (- Pain that spreads beyond the original site) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 408.8 Td (- Normal touch feels painful \(allodynia\)) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 394.8 Td (- Heightened sensitivity to light, sound, or temperature) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 380.8 Td (- Pain persists long after injury should have healed) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 366.8 Td (- Fatigue, poor sleep, brain fog alongside pain) Tj ET
BT /F2 12 Tf 54 337.0 Td (The Biopsychosocial Model of Pain) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 319.0 Td (Pain is influenced by three interacting factors:) Tj ET
BT /F2 11 Tf 54 301.0 Td (Biological) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 285.0 Td (- Tissue health and inflammation) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 271.0 Td (- Nervous system sensitivity) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 257.0 Td (- Sleep quality and physical fitness) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 243.0 Td (- Nutrition and overall health) Tj ET
BT /F2 11 Tf 54 225.0 Td (Psychological) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 209.0 Td (- Thoughts and beliefs about pain) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 195.0 Td (- Mood \(depression, anxiety\)) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 181.0 Td (- Attention and focus on pain) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 167.0 Td (- Catastrophizing vs. acceptance) Tj ET
BT /F2 11 Tf 54 149.0 Td (Social) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 133.0 Td (- Support system and relationships) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 119.0 Td (- Work and financial stress) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 105.0 Td (- Social isolation) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 91.0 Td (- Healthcare experiences) Tj ET
endstream
endobj
