BT /F2 14 Tf 54 712.0 Td (Chapter 6: Mind-Body Techniques) Tj ET
BT /F2 12 Tf 54 674.2 Td (Mindfulness for Pain) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 656.2 Td (Mindfulness meditation has strong evidence for reducing pain perception and suffering. It) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 642.2 Td (works by changing how the brain processes pain signals.) Tj ET
BT /F2 11 Tf 54 614.4 Td (Body Scan Meditation \(15 minutes\)) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 598.4 Td (- Lie comfortably with eyes closed) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 584.4 Td (- Notice breath for 2 minutes) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 570.4 Td (- Bring attention to feet - notice sensations without judgment) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 556.4 Td (- Slowly move attention up through each body part) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 542.4 Td (- When reaching painful areas, breathe INTO the sensation) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 528.4 Td (- Observe pain with curiosity, not resistance) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 514.4 Td (- Continue through entire body to top of head) Tj ET
