100 0 obj
<< /Length 2809 >>
stream
BT /F2 14 Tf 54 712.0 Td (Frequently Asked Questions) Tj ET
BT /F2 11 Tf 54 676.2 Td (Q: Why hasn't my pain gone away even though tests are normal?) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 660.2 Td (Normal imaging does not mean no pain. Chronic pain involves nervous system sensitization -) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 646.2 Td (real neurological changes that don't show on X-rays or MRIs. Your pain is valid regardless) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 632.2 Td (of test results.) Tj ET
BT /F2 11 Tf 54 604.4 Td (Q: Is it safe to exercise with chronic pain?) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 588.4 Td (Yes, with appropriate pacing. Gentle, graded exercise is one of the most evidence-based) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 574.4 Td (treatments for chronic pain. Start well below your limit and increase very gradually.) Tj ET
BT /F2 11 Tf 54 546.6 Td (Q: Will I always have this pain?) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 530.6 Td (Many people experience significant improvement over time with proper management. The) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 516.6 Td (nervous system can recalibrate. Focus on function and quality of life rather than zero) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 502.6 Td (pain.) Tj ET
BT /F2 11 Tf 54 474.8 Td (Q: Are pain medications the answer?) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 458.8 Td (Medications can be part of a management plan but rarely solve chronic pain alone. A) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 444.8 Td (multimodal approach \(movement, psychology, lifestyle, medication\) typically works best.) Tj ET
BT /F2 11 Tf 54 417.0 Td (Q: Why does weather affect my pain?) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 401.0 Td (Barometric pressure changes may affect joint fluid and nerve sensitivity. While the exact) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 387.0 Td (mechanism isn't fully understood, this is a real phenomenon many people experience.) Tj ET
BT /F2 11 Tf 54 359.2 Td (Q: How do I explain chronic pain to family?) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 343.2 Td (Use analogies: 'My alarm system is stuck on - it fires even without danger.' Share) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 329.2 Td (educational resources. Invite them to a doctor's appointment. Be direct about what helps) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 315.2 Td (and what doesn't.) Tj ET
BT /F2 11 Tf 54 287.4 Td (Q: Is chronic pain 'all in my head'?) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 271.4 Td (No. Chronic pain is real and involves measurable changes in the nervous system. The brain) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 257.4 Td (processes all pain - this doesn't make it less real. Anyone suggesting otherwise is) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 243.4 Td (uninformed.) Tj ET
BT /F2 11 Tf 54 215.6 Td (Q: Should I push through pain or rest?) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 199.6 Td (Neither extreme works. Pushing through leads to flares; excessive rest leads to) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 185.6 Td (deconditioning. Pacing - consistent moderate activity with planned rest - is the) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 171.6 Td (evidence-based approach.) Tj ET
endstream
endobj
